name: Let's Meetup and talk Google!

venue.name: Digital Vikings

description:
Join us for first monthly meeting! We will provide an introduction to the group, ourselves, and discuss products and topics announced at this year's Google I/O. Pizza will be provided.

We hope to see you there!
how_to_find_us: The entrance to the space is on the back left of the first floor.

name: Simple Android Wear Interaction Discussion

venue.name: Alexander Graham Bell Building (a Capital One office)

description:
Come join us for an introduction to Android Wear Interactions! Pete Varvarezis will be both presenting and demonstrating on this interactive topic.

Dinner will be provided.

Please RSVP if you plan on attending. We hope to see you there!

Parking and Building Entrance Instructions:

When you arrive, please park in front of the building or at the Amtrak Parking Garage across the street. If you choose to park in front of the building, when you buzz in please say you are here for a meeting with Pete Varvarezis.

Additionally, when you arrive please contact Pete at

(610)[masked] and he will open the doors for you.
how_to_find_us: The office is located next to the Riverfront Market. Our meeting room is located on the first floor, next to the main entrance.

name: An Introduction to Material Design

venue.name: Capital One - Oliver Evans Building

description:
Come join us for an introduction to Material Design, presented by Thomas Belk. Tom will explain the basics of material design while walking the group through a presentation in an app that he built.

Dinner will be provided. 

See you there!

If you have any issues accesssing the bulding or finding the room, please contact Pete at (610)[masked].
how_to_find_us: We will be in the auditorium on the second floor. Please take the stairs in the center of the lobby, past the bathrooms and through the double doors.

name: Google I/O -  Extended Viewing Event

venue.name: Alexander Graham Bell Building (a Capital One office)

description:
Come join us watch the Google I/O Conference on the big screen! 

We will be kicking off the event watching the keynote speaker on Thursday, 5/28 from 12:30pm to 3pm and then continuing to watch the event through the evening, with food and drinks provided. The event will then continue the following day, Friday, 5/29, at 12:30pm until the end of the conference broadcast.

Door prizes will be presented to those who attend the keynote.

We hope to see you there!

name: July GDG Meet-up

venue.name: 1313 Innovation

description:
Our topic is *drum roll* Google I/O!

An overview of the event and a summary of the outcomes by two members who were able to attend the conference in person!

We will also have a social portion to this event as well as food and drinks provided.

Parking: You should be able to find spaces on the street. If you are wary of leaving your car in the open, you can use the Colonial Parking garage at 12th and Orange Streets. It is open until 9pm

Can't wait to see you there!

description:

One of the topics we'll be talking about this week is starting a Study Jam group to take the Udacity Android for Beginners course. The course is a great way to introduce developers to Android or tech newbies. Make sure to let us know if you're interested in joining! 

Hope to see you tomorrow!

name: Google IO (Extended) - Wilmington, DE
description:
Hello GDG Group,

We wanted to invite you to attend Google IO with us here in Wilmington.

Google I/O is an annual developer festival held in California. However, Capital One will be hosting it's own extended version of Google IO. From May 17 - 19, 2017, watch and listen to technical talks, and get a chance to hear more about Google’s latest developer products. 

Google Event Schedule: https://events.google.com/io/schedule/?section=may-17

Space for this event is limited!

To attend, you must RSVP through Eventbrite:
https://www.eventbrite.com/e/google-io-extended-tickets-34140039778
